# Easy Numbers Methodology

Based on Greg Crabtree's Simple Numbers, adapted as Easy Numbers. Nick's proprietary system.
Positioning: CRI teaches Simple Numbers. EasyFlow installs it.

## P&L Waterfall

```
Revenue
minus COGS (materials only. NO labor in COGS. Ever.)
= Gross Margin
minus Direct Labor (includes Owner Direct Labor, Row 23, 50% of owner pay)
= Contribution Margin
minus Marketing
minus Operating Expenses (includes Owner Management Wage, Row 42, 50% of owner pay)
= Pretax Net Income
```

True Pretax Profit = Pretax Net Income + Owner's Market Wage (add-back for diagnostic only)

## Owner Pay Rules

- Split 50/50 on the P&L: Row 23 (Owner Direct Labor) + Row 42 (Owner Management Wage)
- No add-back in the actual P&L. Owner pay is an operating expense, not a distribution.
- Use $30K in all early-stage examples.

## Three Productivity Ratios

| Ratio | Formula | Target |
|---|---|---|
| Direct LPR | Gross Margin / Direct Labor | 2.5x to 3.5x |
| MPR | Gross Margin / Marketing Spend | 5x+ |
| ManPR | Contribution Margin / Management Salaries only | 1.0x+ |

The Excel model uses "LER" internally. Client-facing: always say Productivity Ratios and LPR.
10% pretax profit = the new breakeven. This is not a goal. It is the floor.

## Four Forces Cash Allocation (in order)

1. Tax Reserve
2. Debt Service
3. Core Capital (2 months of operating expenses)
4. Distributions (owner)

Core Capital (Force 3) must be fully funded BEFORE Distributions (Force 4).

## Diagnostic Thresholds

| Metric | Target |
|---|---|
| Direct LPR | 2.5x to 3.5x |
| MPR | 5x+ |
| ManPR | 1.0x+ |
| Pretax Profit % | 10%+ (5-9% Survival, under 5% Crisis) |
| Core Capital | 2 months OpEx |
| ROIC | 50%+ |
| DSCR | 1.25x+ |
| Cash Runway | 8+ weeks |

## Crabtree 3-Bucket Capital

| Bucket | Definition |
|---|---|
| Trade Capital | AR + Inventory + Other Current Assets minus AP, Deferred Revenue, Other Current Liabilities |
| Infrastructure Capital | Net Fixed Assets minus Debt secured by Fixed Assets |
| Buffer Capital | Cash minus Line of Credit Drawn |
